sse2 lrint/lrintf updates:

- adds a configuration option to enable sse2-lrint/lrintf on x86 cpus,

- sse2-lrint/lrintf inlines are now default on x86_64, for simplicity.

commit.message:
index.md: A semicolon becomes a comma.

The semicolon is incorrectly used to join a clause and a phrase.

cmake, autotools: better check for visibility attributes support.

in autotools case, also moves warning flags additions after visibility
checks so that false negatives wouldn't happen and removes dependence on
gnulib's visibility.m4.

Fixes: https://github.com/libsndfile/libsamplerate/issues/154
cmake: Fix shared library ABI on Apple platforms
